agent_answer:
Based on the arXiv help documentation, if your submission has not yet become publicly available (is not announced), you can withdraw it by following these steps:

1. Go to your user page
2. Look for the Delete or Unsubmit option
3. Select either Delete or Unsubmit

Note: If you need to contact arXiv administrators or have any difficulties with the deletion, please do so immediately in your message, including:
- The submission identifier
- An explanation of the problem
- The reason for withdrawal

The system will allow you to modify and later resubmit if needed, and the original submission will still be accessible with the withdrawn version.

task.question: Visit ArXiv Help on how to withdraw an article if the submission is not yet announced.
task.answer: If your submission has not yet become publicly available you may delete or delay it. To do either of these things go to your user page and select either the Delete or Unsubmit icon.
